.TH DICTEE-TRANSCRIBE "1" "April 2026" "dictee 1.3.0"
.SH NAME
dictee-transcribe \- graphical audio file transcription with optional diarization
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictee-transcribe
[\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
PyQt6 graphical interface for transcribing audio files. Supports all ASR backends
(Parakeet, Canary, Vosk, Whisper) via the daemon socket protocol.
.PP
Features include speaker diarization (max 4 speakers), integrated audio player
with speaker segment markers, per-tab translation, and export to text/SRT/JSON.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I FILE
Optional audio file to load on startup. Supported formats: WAV, MP3, FLAC, OGG, M4A, WebM, Opus.
.SH DIARIZATION
Two-phase diarization: phase 1 uses the Sortformer model to detect speakers,
phase 2 sends the full audio to the ASR daemon for transcription with speaker labels.
.PP
A sensitivity slider controls speaker detection threshold (0\-100%).
.SH TRANSLATION
Integrated translation via Google/Bing (translate-shell), Ollama, or LibreTranslate.
Each translation creates a new tab that can be exported independently.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dictee.conf
ASR backend and translation configuration
.TP
.I /tmp/dictee-transcribe.log
Debug log (when DICTEE_DEBUG=true)
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dictee (1),
.BR dictee-setup (1),
.BR transcribe-daemon (1)
